    "description": "本課程主要內容在於說明創意的價值，透過解釋創意思維與運用，進而將創意生活化、工作化與實用化，讓學生了解創意並非遙不可及或僅是單純的天馬行空之想像，進而體會創意對於企業營運的價值。",
    "prerequisites": "無",
    "syllabus": {
        "zh": "1.\t創意的定義<br>2.\t從個人到團隊的創意 <br>3.\t創意義統：管理與產業之意涵<br>4.\t創意的駕馭<br>5.\t創意軌跡<br>6.\t企業發展與組織變革<br>7.\t從創意行銷到創意消費",
        "en": "1.\tDefining Creativity<br>2.\tFrom Individuals to Processes: Creative Teams and Innovation<br>3.\tCreative Systems: Implications for Management and Policy in the Creative Industries<br>4.\tManaging Creative Work through Release and Control<br>5.\tSeeing the Pattern<br>6.\tBusiness Development and Organizational Change<br>7.\tFrom Creative Marketing to Creative Consumption"
